{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/topic-modeling-with-gensim-a5609cefccc", "time": 1683001435.408152, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/topic-modeling-with-gensim-a5609cefccc/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Topic Modeling with Gensim. A guide to get started with\u2026 | by Tara Boyle | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Topic Modeling with Gensim", "description": "Topic modeling is a method for discovering topics that occur in a collection of documents. It can be used for tasks ranging from clustering to dimensionality reduction. A major challenge, however, is\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topic_model", "anchor_text": "Topic modeling", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://radimrehurek.com/gensim/intro.html", "anchor_text": "Gensim\u2019s introduction", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/my-first-twitter-app-1115a327349e", "anchor_text": "Donald Trump Twitter dataset", "paragraph_index": 5}, {"url": "https://radimrehurek.com/gensim/parsing/preprocessing.html", "anchor_text": "preprocessing", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://pyldavis.readthedocs.io/en/latest/", "anchor_text": "PyLDAVis", "paragraph_index": 17}], "all_paragraphs": ["Topic modeling is a method for discovering topics that occur in a collection of documents. It can be used for tasks ranging from clustering to dimensionality reduction.", "Topic models can be useful in many scenarios, including text classification and trend detection.", "A major challenge, however, is to extract high quality, meaningful, and clear topics. Gensim, a Python library, that identifies itself as \u201ctopic modelling for humans\u201d helps make our task a little easier.", "In Gensim\u2019s introduction it is described as being \u201cdesigned to automatically extract semantic topics from documents, as efficiently (computer-wise) and painlessly (human-wise) as possible.\u201d", "To me, this makes it a no-brainer to use for topic modeling.", "We\u2019ll continue using our Donald Trump Twitter dataset. It\u2019s relatively small and easy to work with and covers a very diverse set of topics.", "Given the dataset of tweets, we will try to identify key topics or themes.", "Gensim\u2019s website states it was \u201cdesigned to process raw, unstructured digital texts\u201d and it comes with a preprocessing module for just that purpose.", "The preprocess_string method makes it very easy to prepare text. By default it strips punctuation, HTML tags, multiple white spaces, non-alphabetic characters, and stop words, and even stems the text! It returns a completely processed list of strings:", "Unfortunately, for our twitter dataset, the default might not be the best option: The link was split into two tokens, the second of which appears meaningless.", "Fortunately, we can still use preprocess_string and declare a custom filter variable to select only the those filters we\u2019d like to use:", "This looks better! We\u2019ve pre-processed our text, leaving the link intact.", "Gensim requires that tokens be converted to a dictionary. In this instance a dictionary is a mapping between words and their integer IDs.", "Gensim supports several different transformations, but we will focus on only TF-IDF and LDA here.", "TF-IDF or Term Frequency Inverse Document Frequency is similar to bag-of-word, but it down weights tokens appearing frequently.", "According to Gensim\u2019s documentation, LDA or Latent Dirichlet Allocation, is a \u201ctransformation from bag-of-words counts into a topic space of lower dimensionality. . .LDA\u2019s topics can be interpreted as probability distributions over words.\u201d", "We will first apply TF-IDF to our corpus followed by LDA in an attempt to get the best quality topics.", "We can use PyLDAVis to easily visualize and interpret the topics in our LDA model.", "When interpreting our visualization keep in mind that larger topics indicate they are more frequent and topics that are nearer to each other are more similar.", "We can see that we have 10 topics. Some of the topics have significant overlap. This can indicate that our topics might not be ideal.", "There are several methods we could use to improve our topic segregation. Some potential options are to improve the quality of our pre-processing, change the number of topics, and to add n-grams.", "Here we explored topic modeling and pre-processing with Gensim, just a small portion of what the library has to offer.", "In future articles, we\u2019ll continue exploring topic modeling, including methods for improving the quality of topics.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "I\u2019m passionate about all things data! I\u2019m interested in leveraging data to create business solutions."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fa5609cefccc&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Ftopic-modeling-with-gensim-a5609cefccc&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Ftopic-modeling-with-gensim-a5609cefccc&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav------